The paper deals with a general interpolation problem that has applications in coding theory and security, which suggests that it could belong to sub-categories related to information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), systems and control (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, the focus on computing minimal bases of solutions and the use of Popov normal form suggest that the paper is more likely to belong to the sub-category of symbolic computation (cs.SC), which deals with algorithms and techniques for manipulating mathematical expressions and objects.
